sentences: MacKenzie Lea Porter (born January 29, 1990) is a Canadian country singer, actress and songwriter.

She has released one self-titled album, achieved three Canada Country number ones with "About You", "These Days", and "Seeing Other People", and featured on Dustin Lynch's number one Country Airplay hit "Thinking 'Bout You".
Growing up, she toured in a family band with her brother, 2004 Canadian Idol winner Kalan Porter.
Their grandfather Bob Porter was Member of Parliament for Medicine Hat from 1988 to 1993.
Porter has appeared in numerous films and television productions, including Dinosapien (2007)
Hell on Wheels and Travelers (2016).
She was also named as one of the Top 11 Hottest Vancouver Actors to Watch for 2011 by BC Living magazine.
She was also named as one of the Top 11 Hottest Vancouver Actors to Watch for 2011 by BC Living magazine.
In 2010, she launched a solo career.
Porter was the winner of the 2011 Nashville North Star competition.
In October 2012, Porter released her debut single, "I Wish I'd Known".
Her second single, "Never Gonna Let You", was co-written and produced by Carolyn Dawn Johnson.
Porter was chosen as one of six acts for the inaugural Canadian Country Music Association Discovery Program in 2013.
She was also nominated for the Rising Star Award at the 2013 Canadian Country Music Association Awards.
Her debut album was released on July 15, 2014.
She featured on the song "Circles" on Chris Lane's album Girl Problems in 2016.
